{"type":"message","id":"1bc4051c","parentId":"4d8a6124","timestamp":"2026-05-03T17:32:58.025Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:c7f39628-4f97-47bb-8ec4-70d200938690 Wiki Logging - Rex] Execute: python3 ~/agent-mission-control/scripts/wiki-heartbeat.py rex\n\nThis logs recent conversations to the wiki at ~/agent-mission-control/memory-wiki/daily-logs/. Read the wiki-heartbeat.py script and follow its logic.\nCurrent time: Sunday, May 3rd, 2026 - 1:32 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-05-03 17:32 UTC"}],"timestamp":1777829577973}}
{"type":"message","id":"b26dc881","parentId":"1bc4051c","timestamp":"2026-05-03T17:33:01.415Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to execute a script that logs recent conversations to a wiki. Let me first read the script to understand what it does.","thinkingSignature":"8f7b09b2fc845751904a3bd9468bbc5eb80f4344605dbaa0cfec1bce754d4a89"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dq4uz9ulq0va_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/scripts/wiki-heartbeat.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":148,"output":69,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":16376,"totalTokens":16593,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777829578026,"responseId":"0646b9caa95fad7154b7042a5bf2b432"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0601dc85","parentId":"b26dc881","timestamp":"2026-05-03T17:33:01.487Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dq4uz9ulq0va_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nWiki Heartbeat Logger\nReads OpenClaw session files directly to log conversations to memory-wiki.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport sys\nimport os\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nWIKI_ROOT = Path.home() / \"agent-mission-control\" / \"memory-wiki\"\nLOGS_DIR = WIKI_ROOT / \"daily-logs\"\nSTATE_FILE = WIKI_ROOT / \".heartbeat_logger_state.json\"\n\ndef get_sessions_for_agent(agent_id):\n    \"\"\"Get sessions.json path and parse it.\"\"\"\n    sessions_path = Path.home() / \".openclaw\" / \"agents\" / agent_id / \"sessions\" / \"sessions.json\"\n    if not sessions_path.exists():\n        return {}\n    \n    with open(sessions_path) as f:\n        return json.load(f)\n\ndef get_session_file(agent_id, session_id):\n    \"\"\"Get the .jsonl file path for a session.\"\"\"\n    sessions_dir = Path.home() / \".openclaw\" / \"agents\" / agent_id / \"sessions\"\n    jsonl_file = sessions_dir / f\"{session_id}.jsonl\"\n    if jsonl_file.exists():\n        return jsonl_file\n    return None\n\ndef get_telegram_session_key(sessions):\n    \"\"\"Find the Telegram direct session for an agent.\"\"\"\n    for key in sessions:\n        if \"telegram:direct\" in key and \":main:\" not in key.replace(\"telegram:direct\", \"\"):\n            # This is a sub-agent's telegram session\n            if any(x in key for x in [\":emmy:\", \":finn:\", \":rex:\", \":x:\", \":yoyos:\", \":cody:\", \":dj:\", \":reese:\", \":tt:\"]):\n                return key\n        elif \"telegram:direct\" in key and \":main:\" in key:\n            return key\n    return None\n\ndef read_jsonl_file(file_path):\n    \"\"\"Read a .jsonl file and return list of messages.\"\"\"\n    messages = []\n    try:\n        with open(file_path) as f:\n            for line in f:\n                if line.strip():\n                    try:\n                        msg = json.loads(line)\n                        # Extract the actual message content\n                        if msg.get(\"type\") == \"message\":\n                            messages.append(msg[\"message\"])\n                    except:\n                        pass\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error reading {file_path}: {e}\")\n    return messages\n\ndef extract_conversation_text(messages):\n    \"\"\"Extract conversation pairs from messages.\"\"\"\n    entries = []\n    current_bobby = None\n    \n    for msg in messages:\n        role = msg.get(\"role\", \"\")\n        content = msg.get(\"content\", \"\")\n        \n        # Handle content as list\n        if isinstance(content, list):\n            text_parts = []\n            for c in content:\n                if isinstance(c, dict) and c.get(\"type\") == \"text\":\n                    text_parts.append(c.get(\"text\", \"\"))\n            content = \" \".join(text_parts)\n        \n        if not content or len(content.strip()) < 2:\n            continue\n        \n        # Skip tool results and system messages\n        if role == \"system\":\n            continue\n        \n        if role == \"user\":\n            text = content.strip()\n            # Skip very short messages and tool calls\n            if len(text) > 2 and role != \"toolResult\":\n                current_bobby = text[:1000]\n        elif role == \"assistant\" and current_bobby:\n            # Skip thinking content and tool calls\n            display_content = content[:800] + \"...\" if len(content) > 800 else content\n            entries.append((current_bobby, display_content))\n            current_bobby = None\n    \n    return entries\n\ndef load_state():\n    \"\"\"Load state.\"\"\"\n    if STATE_FILE.exists():\n        with open(STATE_FILE) as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    return {}\n\ndef save_state(state):\n    \"\"\"Save state.\"\"\"\n    with open(STATE_FILE, \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(state, f)\n\ndef log_conversation(agent_id, entries):\n    \"\"\"Log conversation entries to today's daily log.\"\"\"\n    if not entries:\n        return 0\n    \n    today = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n    log_file = LOGS_DIR / f\"{today}.md\"\n    \n    if not log_file.exists():\n        with open(log_file, \"w\") as f:\n            f.write(f\"# {today} - Daily Log\\n\\n---\\n\\n\")\n    \n    new_entries = 0\n    with open(log_file, \"a\") as f:\n        f.write(f\"\\n### {agent_id.upper()} × Bobby\\n**Time:** {datetime.now().strftime('%H:%M')}\\n\\n\")\n        for bobby_msg, agent_msg in entries:\n            f.write(f\"**Bobby:** {bobby_msg}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"**{agent_id.upper()}:** {agent_msg}\\n\\n\")\n            new_entries += 1\n    \n    return new_entries\n\ndef main():\n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        print(\"Usage: wiki-heartbeat.py <agent_id>\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    agent_id = sys.argv[1]\n    state = load_state()\n    state_key = f\"{agent_id}_jsonl_mtime\"\n    \n    sessions = get_sessions_for_agent(agent_id)\n    if not sessions:\n        print(f\"No sessions found for {agent_id}\")\n        return\n    \n    # Find the telegram session\n    telegram_key = get_telegram_session_key(sessions)\n    if not telegram_key:\n        print(f\"No Telegram session found for {agent_id}\")\n        return\n    \n    session_data = sessions[telegram_key]\n    session_id = session_data.get(\"sessionId\")\n    if not session_id:\n        print(f\"No sessionId for {agent_id}\")\n        return\n    \n    # Get the jsonl file\n    jsonl_file = get_session_file(agent_id, session_id)\n    if not jsonl_file:\n        print(f\"No jsonl file found for {agent_id} ({session_id})\")\n        return\n    \n    # Check if file has changed since last sync\n    mtime = jsonl_file.stat().st_mtime\n    if state.get(state_key) == mtime:\n        print(f\"No new messages for {agent_id}\")\n        return\n    \n    # Read messages\n    messages = read_jsonl_file(jsonl_file)\n    if not messages:\n        print(f\"No messages read for {agent_id}\")\n        return\n    \n    # Extract conversation pairs\n    entries = extract_conversation_text(messages)\n    if not entries:\n        print(f\"No conversation entries extracted for {agent_id}\")\n        return\n    \n    # Log to wiki\n    new_logs = log_conversation(agent_id, entries)\n    state[state_key] = mtime\n    save_state(state)\n    \n    print(f\"Logged {new_logs} new entries for {agent_id}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777829581487}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5b054b2","parentId":"0601dc85","timestamp":"2026-05-03T17:33:05.477Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The script:\n1. Takes an agent_id as argument\n2. Reads sessions.json for that agent\n3. Finds a Telegram direct session for that agent\n4. Reads the corresponding .jsonl file\n5. Extracts conversation pairs (user/assistant)\n6. Appends them to today's daily log file in the wiki\n7. Tracks state to avoid re-logging same content\n\nLet me run it for \"rex\".","thinkingSignature":"3c19f469820cf1cdbf8dc087a964b1dfac6c85cddfdfdbff73f51597d45c1fdf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ts328fzcsbc7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 ~/agent-mission-control/scripts/wiki-heartbeat.py rex"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1797,"output":125,"cacheRead":16254,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18176,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777829581487,"responseId":"0646b9cdcc180a48cb293f00e6cc5f85"}}
